{
  "texts": [
    "This could be either because aligned systems are more useful or because alignment research can let dangerous systems appear harmless.",
    "With respect to the first worry, research on alignment and research on making models more powerful are not always cleanly separable.",
    "For instance, the fine-tuning via RLHF used to align ChatGPT makes it better at many kinds of tasks, e.g.",
    "giving correct answers.",
    "Since aligned systems are more useful, there are stronger incentives to accelerate their development and deploy them recklessly.Moving on to the second worry, alignment research might cause us to believe that models are harmless even if they are dangerous."
  ]
}